The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 August is 293,723 (33,853.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 August, there were 701 new confirmed cases (80.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 July, there were 973 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 28% (272 fewer cases).
